| Plot                    =[[Norman Osborn (Earth-TRN1504)|Green Goblin]] attempts to attack [[Mary Jane Watson (Earth-TRN1504)|Mary Jane]] with his glider and bombs, but [[Peter Parker (Earth-TRN1504)|Spider-Man]] saves her just in time. Spider-Man webs up Goblin and the day is saved. 

| Trivia                  =*One of [[Spider-Man: The Peril of Doc Ock|two]] stop motion shorts outsourced to Spite Your Face Productions for promotion for the [[Earth-96283|Raimi Spider-Man films]].{{r|https://web.archive.org/web/20020726021222/http://spiteyourface.com/}}
*Despite [[Spider-Man]]'s name having a hyphen, the title for this short excludes it.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20021203074000/http://www.lego.com:80/eng/studios/screening/movie.asp?id=spiderman</ref>
**The name would be corrected for the sequel.{{r|[[Spider-Man: The Peril of Doc Ock]]}}
*Like its [[Spider-Man: The Peril of Doc Ock|sequel]], this short has 2 different versions. Unlike the second, this shorts two versions are just the scenes in different orders.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gcf7v3C-V94</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q3Oood9Ch3c</ref>
*The terrorist attacks on September 11th, 2001 affected what Green Goblin was able to do. According to the directos, Goblin was not allowed to use his [[Pumpkin Bombs]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1wM8ObaYKCk&t=726s</ref>
